verses.roman:
tabe prakṣālana kaila śrī-jagamohana
bhoga-mandira-ādi tabe kaila prakṣālana

synonyms: tabe—thereafter; prakṣālana—washing; kaila—performed; śrī-jagamohana—in front of the temple; bhoga-mandira—the place where food is offered; ādi—all such places; tabe—then; kaila prakṣālana—washed.
translation: They washed the Jagamohana area and then the place where food was kept. All other places were also washed.
